The paper deals with planar drawings of graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of series-parallel graphs and their properties suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The mention of angular resolution and the number of distinct slopes may indicate a connection to graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the use of upward planar drawings and the optimization of slope angles may suggest a connection to visualization and human-computer interaction (cs.SI).
